args: Whoa! There are so many people here!
And I get to eat with all of them! Hooray!
Yes, His Highness and a number of others\nleft on an expedition a few days ago and\nonly returned to us this morning.
They just keep coming... It's wild!
We are all pleased to see him well;\nhe is our leader, and the one to whom\nwe all look for support.
Welcome back, my darling!\nYou must be starving. Here!
She's passionate about him, certainly.\nEnough so that she chose to change her\nform just to be closer to him.
Mym is a dragon—\nhence the horns and tail.
He even has dragons in love with him?\n{player_name} sure is popular!
I became his vassal because I admire\nall that he is and stands for.
He taught me the meaning of strength,\nafter all.
Learning more about how he thinks has\nreally helped me as a leader.
My life's the bee's knees now,\nand it's all thanks to the big boss.
I used to live for scrapes and bruises\nand not much else—but now I know a gal\ncan live for whatever tickles her fancy!
I was a suspicious figure without memory\nor past, yet he welcomed me into his\nbosom as if I were his own kin.
It is a kindness I can never repay.
Wow!\nHe's special to all of you...
Different things may have led you here,\nbut you all seem to adore and appreciate\n{player_name} equally.
He reminds me of someone I know...
Someone I met back in my world.\nSomeone very dear to me.
He was one of the other founding\nmembers of the Gourmet Guild.
We formed it with Kokkoro and Karyl—\ntwo other friends of ours—but he's\nalways been at its center.
Our guild is like a home to me.
You truly love them, don't you?
Gotta be hard being separated, huh?
I hope you can get back to them soon—\nand we'll do everything we can to help!
Thank you! But as much as I appreciate\nthe thought, I'm actually fine.
In truth, I think I want to stay in this world\nfor a little bit longer.
Sure! After all, I haven't gone on a food\ntour in this world yet!
I haven't even been to the Aquapolis or\nValkaheim yet—and they're BOUND to\nhave some really unique eats!
Going back home without doing that\nwould be a terrible waste.
Hee hee! Don't make me blush!
I do not believe she was lauding you.
Oh, but that's not the only reason\nI want to stick around a bit longer.
I've really taken a shine to this castle.\nBeing here with you all is so nice!
It reminds me of our guildhouse\nback home.
This castle is filled with so much warmth,\nand a person can tell how close you all are\njust by being here.
You welcomed me with open arms when\nyou found me—and I'll always be\nincredibly grateful for that.
So now it's my turn to return the favor!
This is now my second home,\nand it's all thanks to you!
